This modifies the way character data is stored by merging
ranges with single characters and other ranges that are directly
adjacent.

Clarify range simplification code

Use int instead of hex codes for chars in character data

It's easier to work with, and a little quicker to load.

Include single chars right after range to be included in range

This also combines a bunch of ranges because their new last_max will
match the previous of the next range.
Include single chars right before range to be included in range

Combine adjacent ranges in character data to single ranges

The input data files does not always do this. The data files
and the character group tree will be simpler with this changes.
